From ea787e5efef0ae84e31d104cc9297a8f3327fa4b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohit Chamania <mohitc@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 11 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] DEBIAN: Fix FTBFS against GCC 15, which defaults to C23
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Use the standard bool from stdbool.h type instead of a custom one.

Upstream rather recommends to build using ANSI C standard, but this does not
work for Debian because it does not use the vendored version of SuiteSparse,
but rather the packaged version, and the latter is not ANSI C (it uses
C++-style comments).

Bug: https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/bug-glpk/2025-05/msg00000.html
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/1096728
Reviewed-by: Sébastien Villemot <sebastien@debian.org>
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 src/minisat/minisat.h | 5 +----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/minisat/minisat.h b/src/minisat/minisat.h
index 2733e8d..f366f83 100644
--- a/src/minisat/minisat.h
+++ b/src/minisat/minisat.h
@@ -34,10 +34,7 @@
 /*====================================================================*/
 /* Simple types: */
 
-typedef int bool;
-
-#define true  1
-#define false 0
+#include <stdbool.h>
 
 typedef int  lit;
 #if 0 /* by mao */
-- 
2.52.0

